tte — text-encoded 3D rendering engine

USAGE:
    tte view [OPTIONS] <scene.obj>    Orbit a model interactively
    tte [OPTIONS]

VIEW OPTIONS:
    --render KIND    solid (default) or wireframe
    --shading MODE   flat (default) or gouraud (solid only)
    --mode OUTPUT    ascii (default), truecolor, or halfblock (solid only)
    --yaw DEG        Initial orbit azimuth in degrees
    --pitch DEG      Initial orbit elevation in degrees
    --radius F       Initial orbit distance from the model
    --headless       Dump frames to stdout (no terminal control)
    --size WxH       Cell grid size (default: terminal size, or 80x24 headless)
    --frames N       Number of frames to dump in headless mode (default: 1)

KEYS (interactive):
    arrows / hjkl    Orbit the camera
    + = i  /  - o    Zoom in / out
    space            Toggle auto-orbit
    r                Reset the view
    q, Esc, Ctrl-C   Quit

OPTIONS:
    -V, --version    Print version information
    -h, --help       Print this help
